title: Mandatory vaccination - a global trend?
description:
Several European countries are introducing mandatory vaccination, joining a global trend towards penalties and incentives for following recommended vaccination schedules. 
Dr Katie Atwell, Lecturer in the School of Social Sciences, University of Western Australia, discusses the rationale behind this trend. She also explores how success will be measured and, in a subsequent video, suggests that the impact sanctions can sometimes be limited. 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zVS4RHK6Aig&feature=youtu.be
tags: vaccine mandates', 'mandatory vaccination', 'compulsory vaccination', 'health policy', 'public health', 'political science'
